The conditions under which $A+B=C$ are as follows.


(i) If $a+b< 1/2$, then $A=B=C=0$.


(ii) If $a\geq 1/2$ and $b<1/2$, then $B=0$ and $A=C=1$.


(iii) If $a<1/2$ and $b\geq 1/2$, then $A=0$ and $B=C=1$.


(iv) If $a+b\geq 3/2$, then $A=B=1$ and $C=2$.

